Kosterlitz-Thouless Transition

The Physics

The XY Model on a 2D lattice with Hamiltonian:

H = -J Σ cos(θ_i - θ_j)

Features a topological phase transition at T_KT ≈ 0.89 J:

  • T < T_KT: Vortex-antivortex pairs bound, quasi-long-range order
  • T > T_KT: Pairs unbind, free vortices proliferate, disorder

Vortices are detected by the winding number around each plaquette.

XY Lattice Model (T = 0.5 < T_KT)

Frame: 0
Energy: -
Vortices: -
● Vortex (+1) ● Antivortex (-1)

Vortex Pair (T = 0, collapse)

Frame: 0
Separation: -
Energy: -
Logarithmic attraction: E ~ -πJ log(r)
